{
  "text": "In many countries, JW committees are established to cooperate with medical facilities. The committee members mediate between patients and medical staff, and, in some cases, influence the choice of a favourable doctor [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the USA, there is a 24-hour advisory institution available to JW patients and medical staff alike. Some JW congregations have a list of doctors who agree to treat blood-refusing patients [CITATION_4] .",
  "correct_citation": {
